    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This project builds an end-to-end binary classification pipeline to predict whether an employee is experiencing burnout based on workplace and personal factors. We use **LazyPredict** for rapid model benchmarking, **FLAML** for AutoML optimization, and then train and evaluate the **top 3 models** selected from the benchmark results.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The dataset contains features such as work-from-home availability, designation level, resource allocation, and mental fatigue score. We binarize the continuous burn rate into a classification target.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"By completing this notebook you will learn how to:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Convert a continuous target into a meaningful binary classification problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Handle mixed data types (dates, categorical, numeric) in preprocessing\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Use **LazyPredict** to benchmark dozens of classifiers in one call\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Use **FLAML** AutoML to automatically find the best model and hyperparameters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Compare and evaluate the top 3 models with proper classification metrics\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. Analyze errors and derive actionable business insights\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Problem Statement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Employee burnout is a growing concern in modern workplaces. Given a set of organizational and individual attributes, can we predict whether an employee is at high risk of burnout?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We frame this as a **binary classification** task: an employee is labeled as *burned out* (1) if their burn rate exceeds 0.5, and *not burned out* (0) otherwise.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **HR analytics**: Early detection of burnout enables proactive intervention, reducing turnover costs.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Employee well-being**: Identifying high-risk groups helps organizations design targeted wellness programs.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Business impact**: High burnout correlates with decreased productivity and increased absenteeism.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **ML skills**: Demonstrates converting regression-style data into a classification problem with proper threshold selection.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Property | Value |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|----------|-------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Source** | Kaggle — `blurredmachine/are-your-employees-burning-out` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Records** | ~22,750 |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Features** | 9 (mix of categorical, numeric, date) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Target** | `Burn Rate` (continuous 0–1, binarized at 0.5) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Task** | Binary classification |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Key columns:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Date_of_Joining` — employee's join date\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Gender` — Male / Female\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Company_Type` — Service / Product\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `WFH_Setup_Available` — Yes / No\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Designation` — role seniority (0–5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Resource_Allocation` — hours allocated (1–10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Mental_Fatigue_Score` — self-reported fatigue (0–10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Burn_Rate` — target (0.0–1.0)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
