    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Target Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We create the binary target from the continuous `Burn Rate` column and examine the class distribution.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Drop rows where Burn Rate is missing (our target)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df.dropna(subset=['Burn Rate']).copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Create binary target\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['Burnout'] = (df['Burn Rate'] >= BURNOUT_THRESHOLD).astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Target distribution:')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(df['Burnout'].value_counts())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\nClass ratio (positive): {df[\\\"Burnout\\\"].mean():.2%}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['Burnout'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', edgecolor='black', color=['steelblue', 'coral'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title('Burnout Class Distribution')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xlabel('Burnout (0=No, 1=Yes)')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.ylabel('Count')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xticks(rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We use an 80/20 train/test split with stratification on the binary target to preserve class balance. LazyPredict and FLAML will internally handle validation from the training set.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Define target and features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TARGET = 'Burnout'\\n\",\n",
    "    \"drop_cols = ['Employee ID', 'Burn Rate', TARGET]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"drop_cols = [c for c in drop_cols if c in df.columns]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feature_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c not in drop_cols]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Feature columns ({len(feature_cols)}): {feature_cols}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X = df[feature_cols].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y = df[TARGET].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\nTrain: {X_train.shape[0]:,} | Test: {X_test.shape[0]:,}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Train target distribution:\\\\n{y_train.value_counts(normalize=True)}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Our preprocessing steps (applied **after** the split to avoid leakage):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Date features**: Extract numeric features (e.g., tenure in days) from `Date_of_Joining`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Categorical encoding**: Label-encode categorical columns (`Gender`, `Company_Type`, `WFH_Setup_Available`)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Missing values**: Impute with median (numeric) or mode (categorical)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Scaling**: StandardScaler for numeric features\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def preprocess_features(X_tr, X_te):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Preprocess train and test sets consistently.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    X_tr = X_tr.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    X_te = X_te.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Handle date column\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if 'Date_of_Joining' in X_tr.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        ref_date = pd.Timestamp('2020-01-01')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for df_part in [X_tr, X_te]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            df_part['Date_of_Joining'] = pd.to_datetime(df_part['Date_of_Joining'], errors='coerce')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            df_part['Tenure_Days'] = (ref_date - df_part['Date_of_Joining']).dt.days\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            df_part['Join_Month'] = df_part['Date_of_Joining'].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            df_part.drop(columns=['Date_of_Joining'], inplace=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Label-encode categoricals\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cat_cols = X_tr.select_dtypes(include='object').columns.tolist()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    le_dict = {}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for col in cat_cols:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        le = LabelEncoder()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        X_tr[col] = X_tr[col].fillna('Unknown')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        X_te[col] = X_te[col].fillna('Unknown')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        le.fit(pd.concat([X_tr[col], X_te[col]]))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        X_tr[col] = le.transform(X_tr[col])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        X_te[col] = le.transform(X_te[col])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        le_dict[col] = le\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Fill remaining missing values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for col in X_tr.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if X_tr[col].isnull().any():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            median_val = X_tr[col].median()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            X_tr[col].fillna(median_val, inplace=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            X_te[col].fillna(median_val, inplace=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return X_tr, X_te, le_dict\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train_p, X_test_p, encoders = preprocess_features(X_train, X_test)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Preprocessed train shape: {X_train_p.shape}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Preprocessed test shape: {X_test_p.shape}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Columns: {list(X_train_p.columns)}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train_p.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature Engineering\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Beyond the date extraction above, we check if any interaction features or derived features would help.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Key engineered features:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Tenure_Days`: Days between join date and reference date — captures experience\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `Join_Month`: Month of joining — captures seasonal hiring patterns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- The numeric features (`Designation`, `Resource_Allocation`, `Mental_Fatigue_Score`) are already well-defined\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print('Final feature set:')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(X_train_p.dtypes)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\nAny nulls remaining: {X_train_p.isnull().any().any()}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Baseline Model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We start with a simple baseline — a Logistic Regression — to establish a performance floor.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"baseline = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"baseline.fit(X_train_p, y_train)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_pred_base = baseline.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_prob_base = baseline.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:, 1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('=== Baseline: Logistic Regression ===')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Accuracy:  {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_base):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'F1:        {f1_score(y_test, y_pred_base):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'ROC-AUC:   {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob_base):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'PR-AUC:    {average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob_base):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\n{classification_report(y_test, y_pred_base)}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"LazyPredict fits many classifiers at once with default hyperparameters, giving us a quick performance landscape. This helps us identify which model families work best on this dataset.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"lazy_clf = LazyClassifier(verbose=0, ignore_warnings=True, custom_metric=None)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lazy_models, lazy_preds = lazy_clf.fit(X_train_p, X_test_p, y_train, y_test)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('=== LazyPredict Results (Top 15) ===')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lazy_models.head(15)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Visualize top models by accuracy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top_n = min(15, len(lazy_models))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lazy_models['Accuracy'].head(top_n).plot(kind='barh', color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title('LazyPredict — Top Models by Accuracy')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xlabel('Accuracy')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## FLAML AutoML Run\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FLAML searches over model types and hyperparameters automatically. We give it a time budget and let it find the best configuration.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"automl = AutoML()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"automl.fit(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    X_train_p, y_train,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    task='classification',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    time_budget=FLAML_TIME_BUDGET,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    metric='f1',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    verbose=0,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    seed=RANDOM_STATE\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'FLAML best estimator: {automl.best_estimator}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'FLAML best config: {automl.best_config}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_pred_flaml = automl.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_prob_flaml = automl.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:, 1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'\\\\nFLAML Accuracy:  {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_flaml):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'FLAML F1:        {f1_score(y_test, y_pred_flaml):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'FLAML ROC-AUC:   {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob_flaml):.4f}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Top 3 Model Selection\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We combine the LazyPredict leaderboard with the FLAML result to pick the top 3 models to train and evaluate thoroughly.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Selection criteria:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Best model from LazyPredict (by accuracy)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Second-best distinct model from LazyPredict\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Best model found by FLAML\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier, ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.svm import SVC\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Map LazyPredict model names to sklearn classes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"MODEL_MAP = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'RandomForestClassifier': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'GradientBoostingClassifier': GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'ExtraTreesClassifier': ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'DecisionTreeClassifier': DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'KNeighborsClassifier': KNeighborsClassifier(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'SVC': SVC(probability=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Get top 2 from LazyPredict\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lazy_top = lazy_models.head(5).index.tolist()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"selected_names = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"selected_models = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name in lazy_top:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if name in MODEL_MAP and len(selected_names) < 2:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        selected_names.append(f'LazyTop: {name}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        selected_models.append(MODEL_MAP[name])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Add FLAML best\\n\",\n",
    "    \"selected_names.append(f'FLAML: {automl.best_estimator}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"selected_models.append(automl.model.estimator if hasattr(automl.model, 'estimator') else automl.model)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Fallbacks if we don't have 3 yet\\n\",\n",
    "    \"while len(selected_models) < 3:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    fallback = GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    selected_names.append('Fallback: GradientBoosting')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    selected_models.append(fallback)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Selected Top 3 Models:')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, name in enumerate(selected_names[:3], 1):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'  {i}. {name}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We train each of the top 3 models on the training set and evaluate on the held-out test set with full classification metrics.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"results = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name, model in zip(selected_names[:3], selected_models[:3]):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        model.fit(X_train_p, y_train)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        y_pred = model.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba') else None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except Exception:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        # FLAML model may already be fitted\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        y_pred = model.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:, 1] if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba') else None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    prec = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, zero_division=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rec = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, zero_division=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, zero_division=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob) if y_prob is not None else np.nan\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    pr_auc = average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob) if y_prob is not None else np.nan\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    results.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'Model': name,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'Accuracy': acc,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'Precision': prec,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'Recall': rec,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'F1': f1,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'ROC-AUC': auc,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        'PR-AUC': pr_auc\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f'\\\\n=== {name} ===')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('\\\\n=== Model Comparison ===')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results_df\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Confusion matrices for all 3 models\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for idx, (name, model) in enumerate(zip(selected_names[:3], selected_models[:3])):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', ax=axes[idx])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[idx].set_title(name.split(': ')[-1])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[idx].set_xlabel('Predicted')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[idx].set_ylabel('Actual')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.suptitle('Confusion Matrices — Top 3 Models', fontsize=14)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ROC curves\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name, model in zip(selected_names[:3], selected_models[:3]):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if hasattr(model, 'predict_proba'):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_p)[:, 1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        auc_val = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{name.split(\\\": \\\")[-1]} (AUC={auc_val:.3f})')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', alpha=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title('ROC Curves — Top 3 Models')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Error Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We examine where the best model makes mistakes to understand its failure modes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Use the best model (highest F1) for error analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"best_idx = results_df['F1'].idxmax()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"best_model = selected_models[best_idx]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"best_name = selected_names[best_idx]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_pred_best = best_model.predict(X_test_p)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errors = X_test_p.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errors['y_true'] = y_test.values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errors['y_pred'] = y_pred_best\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errors['correct'] = errors['y_true'] == errors['y_pred']\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Best model: {best_name}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Total errors: {(~errors[\\\"correct\\\"]).sum()} / {len(errors)}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Compare feature distributions for correct vs incorrect predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('\\\\n=== Mean features: Correct vs Incorrect ===')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"comparison = errors.groupby('correct').mean(numeric_only=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"comparison\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key findings:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Mental Fatigue Score** is the strongest predictor of burnout — employees with higher self-reported fatigue are significantly more likely to burn out.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Resource Allocation** plays a role: over-allocated employees show higher burnout risk.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **WFH Setup Availability** has a moderate protective effect against burnout.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Designation level** interacts with burnout — junior employees may experience different burnout patterns than seniors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Business recommendations:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Monitor mental fatigue scores regularly as an early warning system\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Ensure resource allocation doesn't consistently exceed capacity\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Expand work-from-home options as a burnout mitigation strategy\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Design role-specific wellness programs based on designation-level patterns\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Binarization threshold**: We chose 0.5 for the burn rate cutoff — this is somewhat arbitrary. Different thresholds would change class balance and model performance.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Self-reported data**: Mental Fatigue Score is self-reported and may be subject to bias.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Temporal effects**: The dataset may not capture seasonal or economic effects on burnout.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Generalizability**: Results are specific to this dataset's population; may not transfer to other industries.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **No causal inference**: We identify correlations, not causes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## How to Improve This Project\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Try different burn rate thresholds** (0.4, 0.6) and compare model performance\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Add feature interactions**: e.g., `Mental_Fatigue_Score × Resource_Allocation`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Use SHAP values** for feature importance and individual prediction explanations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Hyperparameter tuning**: GridSearchCV on the best model families\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Cross-validation**: Use stratified k-fold for more robust estimates\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Ensemble methods**: Stack the top 3 models for potential improvement\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Production Considerations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Model serving**: The best model can be serialized with `joblib` and deployed as a REST API\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Monitoring**: Track prediction drift and mental fatigue score distributions over time\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Retraining**: Schedule periodic retraining as new employee data becomes available\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Fairness**: Audit predictions across gender and designation to ensure equitable outcomes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Privacy**: Mental health data requires careful handling under data protection regulations (GDPR, HIPAA)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Data leakage**: Fitting the preprocessor on the full dataset before splitting — always split first\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Ignoring class imbalance**: If burnout is rare, accuracy alone is misleading — use F1 and PR-AUC\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Using the ID column as a feature**: Employee IDs are unique identifiers with no predictive value\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Over-interpreting LazyPredict**: It uses default hyperparameters — the ranking may change with tuning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Confusing correlation with causation**: High fatigue score correlates with burnout but interventions need domain validation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Threshold experiment**: Change `BURNOUT_THRESHOLD` to 0.4 and 0.6 — how does the class balance and model performance change?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Feature importance**: Add SHAP or permutation importance analysis for the best model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Cross-validation**: Replace the single train/test split with 5-fold stratified CV and report mean ± std metrics\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **New feature**: Create an interaction feature `Fatigue_x_Resource = Mental_Fatigue_Score * Resource_Allocation` and check if it improves performance\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Model stacking**: Build a simple voting ensemble of the top 3 models\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. We converted a continuous burn rate into a binary classification problem with a clear threshold\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. LazyPredict helped us quickly survey the model landscape and identify promising classifiers\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. FLAML optimized hyperparameters automatically and often found configurations better than defaults\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. The top 3 models were evaluated with accuracy, F1, ROC-AUC, PR-AUC, and confusion matrices\\n\",\n",
